---
title: 'Pyramid Series'
description: '$framework Pyramid Series uses the height of sections to show the proportions of a value over a category of values.'
---

A Pyramid Series is a triangular shaped visualization that uses the height of each segment to represent its value as a proportion of the whole.

## Simple Pyramid

{% chartExampleRunner title="Pyramid Chart" name="simple-pyramid" type="generated" /%}

To create a Pyramid Series, use the `pyramid` series type.

```js
series: [
    {
        type: 'pyramid',
        stageKey: 'group',
        valueKey: 'value'
    },
],
```

In this configuration:

-   `stageKey` defines the categories, each of which is mapped to segments in the pyramid.
-   `valueKey` provides the numerical values, determining the height of each segment.

## Horizontal Pyramid

{% chartExampleRunner title="Horizontal Pyramid Chart" name="horizontal-pyramid" type="generated" /%}

To create a horizontal Pyramid Series, set the `direction` to `horizontal`.

```js
{
    direction: 'horizontal',
}
```

## Reverse Pyramid

{% chartExampleRunner title="Reverse Pyramid Chart" name="reverse-pyramid" type="generated" /%}

To reverse a Pyramid Series, set `reverse` to `true`.

```js
{
    reverse: 'true',
}
```

## Customisation

### Fills

{% chartExampleRunner title="Pyramid Fills" name="pyramid-fills" type="generated" /%}

The colours in a Pyramid Series can be customised with the `fills` property.

```js
{
    fills: ['#5C6BC0', '#3F51B5', '#303F9F', '#1A237E'],
}
```

### Shape

The shape of the triangle can be set using the `aspectRatio` property.

